div1.l:
May-be they only seem to me what they are, (as doubtless they indeed but seem,) as from my 
present point of view—And might prove, (as of course they would,) naught of what they appear, 
or naught any how, from entirely changed points of view;

Then my lands engrossed me—Lands of the prairies, Ohio's land, the southern savannas, 
engrossed me—For them I would live—I would be their  
orator;

Then I met the examples of the old and new heroes—I heard of warriors, sailors, and all 
dauntless persons—And it seemed to me that I too had it in me to be as dauntless as any—and 
would be so;
